    description:
      '<p><strong>Applications only accepted at</strong> <a href="https://www.applitrack.com/sau33/onlineapp/default.aspx">www.sau33.com/jobs</a></p>\n<p><em>This job is part of the Raymond Education Association and is governed by the collective bargaining agreement.&nbsp; For more information about the terms and conditions of the position please click <a href="https://www.sau33.com/site/handlers/filedownload.ashx?moduleinstanceid=23&amp;dataid=4599&amp;FileName=REA%202018-2021%20FINAL%20with%20MOU%20and%20Side%20Letter.pdf">here.</a></em></p>\n<p><strong>The Speech and Language Pathologist</strong> will meet all qualifications and behavior standards as set by the State of New Hampshire authority.&nbsp; In accordance with license requirements and the performances expectations of the Raymond School District, all Speech and Language Pathologist shall meet the following employment criteria.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The minimum of a Master&rsquo;s Degree from an accredited college or university unless Provisional License is issued</li>\n<li>A valid New Hampshire License or&nbsp;Provisional License from the New Hampshire Office of Allied Health Professionals</li>\n<li>A completed credential file that meets Raymond School District&rsquo;s standards.</li>\n<li>Professional verification of successful Speech and Language Pathology performance and/or student experience Evidence of the willingness and the ability to comply with the standards for ethical and professional performance established by the New Hampshire State Board of Education.</li>\n<li>Evidence of the willingness and the ability to comply with the standards for ethical and professional performance established by the New Hampshire Office of Allied Health Professionals</li>\n<li>Interview/file data will include evidence of sensitivity and respect for others and verification of the demonstrated ability to serve as a positive role model for youth.</li>\n<li>Such alternatives to the above qualification as the Board may find appropriate and acceptable</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',
